Cebu Air, SM Investments: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 
2011-05-06T01:13:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/cebu-air-sm-investments-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close,
unless stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 1.2 percent to
4,248.68.  Banks, Builders: The Philippine central bank increased
borrowing costs for the second time this year, raising the rate
it pays lenders for overnight deposits to 4.50 percent from 4.25
percent, the monetary authority said yesterday.  Banco De Oro
Unibank Inc. (BDO)  , the nation’s largest lender, was
unchanged at 57.45 pesos.  Ayala Land Inc. (ALI)   fell 0.9
percent to 16.32 pesos.  Cebu Air Inc. (CEB)  : The country’s largest budget
carrier flew more than a million passengers in April, it said in
a statement yesterday.  The stock fell 1.7 percent to 89.50 pesos.  SM Investments Corp. (SM)  : The owner of the  Philippines ’
largest mall operator and lender said first-quarter net income
rose 13 percent to 5.37 billion pesos. The company is confident
it will meet its targets for the succeeding quarters, SM
President Harley Sy said in a statement, without saying what its
targets are.  The stock fell 0.9 percent to 560 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cecilia Yap in Manila at   cyap19@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
